	<div class="explainer-card__content">
		

<p>In many communities, treatment plants collect used water, purify it and send it back into the delivery system, mostly for irrigation and industrial purposes. In 2015, California recycled about <a href="https://www.waterboards.ca.gov/water_issues/programs/grants_loans/water_recycling/munirec.shtml">714,000 acre-feet</a>, primarily for landscaping and irrigation. Sixteen percent, about 114,000 acre-feet, was used to recharge groundwater basins.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>



<p>Water recycling is often termed a “drought-proof” supply, and state initiatives aim to be reusing about 2.5 million acre-feet annually within a decade. <br></p>



