	<div class="explainer-card__content">
		

<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://calmatters.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/02/BANG_FarmIrrigation_022620_03.jpg?w=1024" alt="Sprinklers water a field of poblano peppers at B&amp;T Farms in Gilroy, Calif., on Tuesday, April 9, 2019. Photo by Randy Vazquez, Bay Area News Group" class="wp-image-102963" srcset="https://calmatters.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/02/BANG_FarmIrrigation_022620_03.jpg?w=2000 2000w, https://calmatters.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/02/BANG_FarmIrrigation_022620_03.jpg?w=300 300w, https://calmatters.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/02/BANG_FarmIrrigation_022620_03.jpg?w=768 768w, https://calmatters.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/02/BANG_FarmIrrigation_022620_03.jpg?w=1024 1024w, https://calmatters.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/02/BANG_FarmIrrigation_022620_03.jpg?w=1536 1536w, https://calmatters.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/02/BANG_FarmIrrigation_022620_03.jpg?w=460 460w, https://calmatters.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/02/BANG_FarmIrrigation_022620_03.jpg?w=321 321w, https://calmatters.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/02/BANG_FarmIrrigation_022620_03.jpg?w=780 780w, https://calmatters.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/02/BANG_FarmIrrigation_022620_03.jpg?w=858 858w, https://calmatters.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/02/BANG_FarmIrrigation_022620_03.jpg?w=794 794w" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" /><figcaption>Sprinklers water a field of poblano peppers at B&amp;T Farms in Gilroy, Calif., on Tuesday, April 9, 2019. Photo by Randy Vazquez, Bay Area News Group</figcaption></figure>



<p>Some farmers use water inefficiently, but in general, they try to squeeze as much “crop per drop” as possible. Many growers have retired flood irrigation and wasteful sprinklers and adopted drip irrigation systems. They also use technology that autonomously monitors soil moisture and remotely opens and closes water valves.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Almond growers, for example, grow each nut with one-third less water than 20 years ago. However, because acreage has <a href="https://www.nass.usda.gov/Statistics_by_State/California/Publications/Specialty_and_Other_Releases/Almond/Acreage/201904almac.pdf">more than doubled</a>, the industry still uses more water than it did.</p>

	</div>

	<div class="explainer-card-footer">
		<span class="explainer-card__footer-copyright">&copy; 2020</span>
		<img class="explainer-card-footer__logo" src="https://calmatters.org/wp-content/themes/calmatters/assets/svg/calmatters-logo.svg">
	</div>
</div>



<div class="explainer-card" id="7101c970-4f72-11ea-9723-33b074c57375">
			<div class="explainer-sponsored-by">
			<span class="explainer-sponsored-by__label">CalMatters Explainers Are Presented By</span>
			<img width="465" height="193" src="https://calmatters.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/01/EdisonLogo.png?fit=465%2C193&#038;resize=465%2C193" class="attachment-full size-full" alt="" srcset="https://calmatters.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/01/EdisonLogo.png?w=465 465w, https://calmatters.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/01/EdisonLogo.png?w=300 300w, https://calmatters.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/01/EdisonLogo.png?w=460 460w, https://calmatters.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/01/EdisonLogo.png?w=380 380w" sizes="(max-width: 465px) 100vw, 465px" data-recalc-dims="1" />		</div>
		<h2 class="explainer-card-title">How is President Trump affecting California’s water problems? </h2>

	<div class="social-share -horizontal">
